      <h1>Grow Avocado Tree At Home</h1>

      <h2><em>It's easy & fun</em></h2>

      <div class="intro-txt">
        <p>
          Do you enjoy guacamole? How about an avocado sandwich with hummus and
          falafel? Well, next time you are preparing such a lovely meal with
          avocado, don't just throw away the seed - use it to grow your own
          avocado tree at home! It's easy and fun, takes a little effort, a lot
          of patience and kind of becomes addictive. Trust me, soon enough you
          will have an avocado trees family in your home!
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="cta-txt">
        <p>Follow this simple steps as illustrated in the picture above and grow your avocado tree:</p>
      </div>

      <ul>
        <li>👉 Remove and clean pit</li>
        <li>👉 Locate which end is "up" and which end is "down"</li>
        <li>👉 Pierce with three toothpicks</li>
        <li>👉 Place seed half-submerged in a glass of water</li>
        <li>👉 Wait for your avocado seed to sprout</li>
        <li>👉 Pot in soil when tree is about 15cm tall</li>
        <li>👉 Water and watch it grow</li>
        <li>👉 Pinch out top leaves to encourage it to grow higher</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="cta-txt">
